asset.hookText:
See more: http://TheBlaze.com/TV.

In 1930, at the Toll House Inn, Ruth Wakefield ran out of baker's chocolate and was forced to improvise - and what happened next, became a moment that changed snacking forever. Nestle bought the recipe and the Toll House name, and the rest is history.  This is an "illuminating moment in American history" (as first seen on TheBlaze TV show "Liberty Treehouse").
